Hexagonal architecture, invented by Alistair Cockburn in 2005, organizes your app into layers like a hexagon (hence the name). The idea is to keep the core domain (your business rules) isolated from external stuff like databases, user interfaces or APIs.

Not just a doc. also a codebase Repo!

https://github.com/jmcastellanojimenez/hexagonal/blob/master/Hexagonal_Architecture_with_Spring_Boot_A_Beginners_Guide.md
